bug.short_desc: Hercules Studio package produces weird output. re-building creates a normal product
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1183139 Watch as each line contains artifacts from the longest line so far
Description of problem: Log lines at the main window contain leftovers from previous lines. for example: line1: 123456 line2: 789
the output is: 123456 789456
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): hercstudio 1.5.0
How reproducible: By installing hercstudio and watching the log lines printed on the main window. Problem does not heppwn when building the binary from source file on the same installation.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora 24 Workstation 2. Install Hercstudio 3. run HerculeStudio from the command line or invoke from the gui menu 4. Create a minimal configuration file: File/New.../Ok/(name)/Save 5. Press on the "Power On" white button
Actual results: Each short line contains leftover from the previous long line
Expected results: Each line contains just the data of that line.
Additional info: 1. When building hercules studio on Fedora 24, this problem does not happen. The problem is only with the package from the Fedora 24 repository. 2. Further info (with pictures) can be found on Hercules Studio support site: https://groups.yahoo.com/neo/groups/hercstudio/info
hercstudio-1.5.0-7.fc24 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 24. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-1e0de7b752

hercstudio-1.5.0-7.fc24 has been pushed to the Fedora 24 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report. You can provide feedback for this update here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2016-1e0de7b752
In hercstudio-1.5.0-7.fc24.x86_64 the problem is gone.
